<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>SURF'S UP!</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20070629.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<br>
<b>Friday, June 29, 2007</b> &mdash; Attention citizens! Surfboard shaper Kainoa Kalepa made a big announcement today!<br><br>He has invited all of Millsberry to surf the waves at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=486">Okalani Island</a>, a tropical destination not too far from here.<br><br>&quot;I made a point to visit Millsberry because I&#039;d heard rumors of an island with great waves nearby,&quot; explained Kainoa. &quot;No one knows about it except for hardcore surfers. It&#039;s not on any map. I checked it out and knew I had to tell you guys about it. The waves are amazing!&quot;<br>
<br>
Kainoa has scouted out four great spots on Okalani for citizens to learn the art of surfing. He&#039;ll teach you cool moves as he sees you improve. Do you think you can pull off a Hang Ten? Will you be able to masterfully surf the first three locations before tackling the most difficult, Radical Reef? You&#039;ll just have to take up Kai&#039;s challenge to find out!<br><br>So how do you get there? Just go to the arcade or head <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/main_map.phtml?location=downtown">downtown</a> as if you were going to Sylvane Lake, and Kainoa will whisk you over to the island. Once you&#039;re there, he&#039;ll provide you with surfboards that he shaped, and you&#039;ll be all ready to rip it up in style!<br><br>&quot;It&#039;s the perfect place for people just learning to surf, or for pros to practice their gnarly moves,&quot; Kai added. &quot;It&#039;s beautiful and quiet year-round. I may not make it around the world like I&#039;d planned...I love it here!&quot;<br><br>Citizens are extremely excited, and Kai&#039;s enthusiasm is contagious. At the end of his announcement, he flashed the sign for &quot;hang loose,&quot; with his thumb and pinkie pointing outward, and received cheers.<br><br>What a great surprise for us this summer. See you at the island!</div>


<br><hr><br>

<div id='gazette_story'>
<div align='center'><font size='3'><b>FOURTH OF JULY</b></font><br>
</div>
<br>
Independence Day is right around the corner. How will you show your patriotic spirit?<br><br>For one, you could have a BBQ with friends and wear red, white, and blue gear. Pick up cool Fourth of July hats, shirts, and decorations at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=3">Furniture</a> and <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing</a> stores today. There are tons of ways to make your home a festive place to celebrate. <br><br>While stocking up on stuff downtown, stop by the Post Office and send a <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/post_office/?action=greetings&cat=July%204th">Fourth of July greeting card</a>. There are many designs to choose from!</div>
